                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/21192",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=fab",
                        "name": "fab",
                        "displayName": "Fabien MARTY",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I agree with you, this could be an option of the Sqlite backend",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=fab",
                        "name": "fab",
                        "displayName": "Fabien MARTY",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-04-19T03:29:00.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-04-19T03:29:00.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/25656",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thing2b",
                        "name": "thing2b",
                        "displayName": "thing2b",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "It would be great to use SQLite 3.x databases.\n\nWhat I can not understand is why Zend_Cache_Backend_Sqlite makes native database calls when calls could be made through Zend_Db_Adapter_Pdo_Sqlite. If I am correct, Zend_Db_Adapter_Pdo_Sqlite supports SQLite2 and SQLite3 databases. Surely making calls on a Zend_Db_Adapter would make things more flexable?\n\nI think Zend_Cache_Backend_Sqlite should be able to be constructed with a path to a Sqlite file OR a Zend_Db_Adapter. Although it might not be wise to use many other Zend_Db_Adapter types, the choice should be mine.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thing2b",
                        "name": "thing2b",
                        "displayName": "thing2b",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-11-04T13:45:14.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-11-04T13:45:14.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/32092",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=mabe",
                        "name": "mabe",
                        "displayName": "Marc Bennewitz (private)",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Hi,\n\nI'm working on a Zend_Cache refactoring proposal.\nThis would handle all SQLite versions and php adapters.\n\nPlease take a look and tell your opinions.\n\nPS: A native sqlite call is much faster and some sql's ( e.g. CREATE ) are not same on all databases ;)",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=mabe",
                        "name": "mabe",
                        "displayName": "Marc Bennewitz (private)",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-06-22T23:31:01.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-06-22T23:31:01.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/32660",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=fab",
                        "name": "fab",
                        "displayName": "Fabien MARTY",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "change Assignee because I'm inactive now",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=fab",
                        "name": "fab",
